[{"id":39502,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Communication System","question":"","options":["$80 \\mathrm{~km}$","$16 \\mathrm{~km}$","$40 \\mathrm{~km}$","$64 \\mathrm{~km}$"],"answer":0,"solution":"Maximum distance on earth where object can be detected is $\\mathrm{d}$, then\n$\\begin{array}{ll} \n& (h+R)^2=d^2+R^2 \\\\\n\\Rightarrow & d^2=h^2+2 R h \\\\\n\\text { since } & h < < R, \\quad \\Rightarrow d^2=2 h R \\\\\n\\Rightarrow & d=\\sqrt{2(500)\\left(6.4 \\times 10^6\\right)}=80 \\mathrm{~km}\n\\end{array}$<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/CJx5bNuxeOmXeKmpIErUaSzeDcpis2chmoM5uUIZpU0.original.fullsize.png\"><br>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2012 (Offline)","image":null},{"id":39476,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Communication System","question":"","options":["$\\left(9+\\sin \\left(2.5 \\pi \\times 10^{5} \\mathrm{t}\\right)\\right) \\sin \\left(2 \\pi \\times 10^{4} \\mathrm{t}\\right) \\mathrm{V}$","$\\left(1+9 \\sin \\left(2 \\pi \\times 10^{4} \\mathrm{t}\\right)\\right) \\sin \\left(2.5 \\pi \\times 10^{5} \\mathrm{t}\\right) \\mathrm{V}$","$\\left(9+\\sin \\left(2 \\pi \\times 10^{4} t\\right)\\right) \\sin \\left(2.5 \\pi \\times 10^{5} \\mathrm{t}\\right) \\mathrm{V}$","$\\left(9+\\sin \\left(4 \\pi \\times 10^{4} t\\right)\\right) \\sin \\left(5 \\pi \\times 10^{5} \\mathrm{t}\\right) \\mathrm{V}$"],"answer":2,"solution":"After analysing the graph we may conclude that\r\n\r\n(i) Amplitude varies as $8-10 \\mathrm{~V}$ or $9 \\pm 1$\r\n\r\n(ii) Two time period as\r\n\r\n$100 \\mu$ s (signal wave) $\\& 8 \\mu$ (carrier wave)\r\n\r\nSo, equation of AM signal is\r\n\r\n$\\left[9 \\pm 1 \\sin \\left(\\frac{2 \\pi t}{T_{1}}\\right) \\sin \\left(\\frac{2 \\pi t}{T_{2}}\\right)\\right]$\r\n\r\n$=\\left[9 \\pm \\sin \\left(2 \\pi \\times 10^{4} \\mathrm{t}\\right)\\right] \\sin \\left(2.5 \\pi \\times 10^{5} \\mathrm{t}\\right) \\mathrm{V}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (11 Jan Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":39479,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Com