/mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>6400</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>0.031458</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">k</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math><br /><math><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">h</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi></mrow></msub><mo>&#8776;</mo><mn>32</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (08 Apr Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":39499,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Communication System","question":"","options":["$\\omega_c$ and $\\sqrt{\\omega_c^2+\\omega_m^2}$","$\\omega_c, \\omega_c+\\omega_m$ and $\\omega_c-\\omega_m$","$\\omega_c$ and $\\omega_m$","$\\omega_c$ and $\\sqrt{\\omega_c \\omega_m}$"],"answer":1,"solution":"The frequencies present in amplitude modulated wave are :\nCarrier frequency $=\\omega_c$\nUpper side band frequency $=\\omega_c+\\omega_m$\nLower side band frequency $=\\omega_c-\\omega_m$.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2012 (19 May Online)","image":null},{"id":39453,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Communication System","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>200</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>kHz</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>500</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>kHz</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>100</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>kHz</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn></math>"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>Bandwidth <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msub><mi>f</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></msub></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>5</mn></msup><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>Hz</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>200</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>kHz</mi></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (25 Jul Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":39430,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Communication System","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<blockquote><p>Maximum range of TV transmission&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>d</mi><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>2</mn><mi>R</mi><mi>h</mi></msqrt></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>d</mi><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>2</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>6400</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mi>h</mi><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup></msqrt></math>&nbsp;(here,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi></math> in <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math>)</p><p>Maximum area of TV transmission</p><p>Area <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mi>&#960;</mi><msup><mi>d</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>&#960;</mi><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>6400</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">h</mi><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfenced><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi>km</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math></p><p>Now,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>6</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>03</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>100000</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>100</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mi>&#960;</mi><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>6400</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>h</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>6</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>03</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>5</mn></msup></mrow><mrow><mn>10</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mi>&#960;</mi><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>128</mn></mrow></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>150</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math></p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (25 Jul Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":39448,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Communication System","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>80</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>km</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>144</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>km</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>57</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>28</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>km</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>45</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>km</mi></math>"],"answer":2,"solution":"<p>The formula of range of the antenna is given by the formula,<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>2</mn><mi>R</mi><msub><mi>h</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></msqrt><mo>+</mo><msqrt><mn>2</mn><mi>R</mi><msub><mi>h</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></msqrt></math>., here&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>R</mi></math>&nbsp;is the radius of the earth then,&nbsp;putting the values, the range <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>57</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>28</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>km</mi></math>.</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (26 Aug Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":39498,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Communication System","question":"","options":["$C_m(t)=A\\left(1+\\sin \\omega_m t\\right) \\sin \\omega_c t$ and 2","$C_m(t)=A\\left(1+\\sin \\omega_m t\\right) \\sin \\omega_m t$ and 1","$C_m(t)=A\\left(1+\\sin \\omega_m t\\right) \\sin \\omega_c t$ and 1","$C_m(t)=A\\left(1+\\sin \\omega_c t\\right) \\sin \\omega_m t$ and 2"],"answer":2,"solution":"Modulation index\n$$\n\\mathrm{m}_{\\mathrm{a}}=\\frac{\\mathrm{E}_{\\mathrm{m}}}{\\mathrm{E}_{\\mathrm{c}}}=\\frac{\\mathrm{A}}{\\mathrm{A}}=1\n$$\nEquation of modulated signal $\\left[\\mathrm{C}_{\\mathrm{m}}(\\mathrm{t})\\right]$\n$$\n=\\mathrm{E}_{(\\mathrm{C})}+\\mathrm{m}_{\\mathrm{a}} \\mathrm{E}_{(\\mathrm{C})} \\sin \\omega_{\\mathrm{m}}^{\\mathrm{t}}\n$$\n$=\\mathrm{A}\\left(1+\\sin \\mathrm{w}_{\\mathrm{C}} \\mathrm{t}\\right) \\sin \\omega_{\\mathrm{m}} \\mathrm{t}$\n$\\left(\\right.$ As $\\left.\\mathrm{E}_{(\\mathrm{C})}=\\mathrm{A} \\sin \\omega_{\\mathrm{c}} \\mathrm{t}\\right)$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2013 (09 Apr Online)","image":null},{"id":39490,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Communication System","question":"","options":["3","5","6","2"],"answer":0,"solution":"Band width for Music signal <math> <mrow> <mo>=</mo><mn>15200</mn><mo>−</mo><mn>10200</mn></mrow> </math> <math> <mrow> <mo>=</mo><mn>5000</mn><mtext> </mtext><mi>H</mi><mi>z</mi></mrow> </math><br /><br />Band width for speech signal <math> <mrow> <mo>=</mo><mn>2700</mn><mo>−</mo><mn>200</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>2500</mn><mi>H</mi><mi>z</mi></mrow> </math><br /><br />Band with for Both = 2500+5000=7500 Hz<br /><br />Band with for Human speech =2500 Hz<br /><br />Required&nbsp;Ratio <math><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>7500</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>2500</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfrac></math>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2016 (09 Apr Online)","image":null},{"id":39434,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Communication System","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>II</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>III</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>IV</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>IV</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>III</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>II</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>IV</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>III</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>II</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>II</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>IV</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>III</mi></math>"],"answer":2,"solution":"<p>Television&nbsp;signal&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8594;</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>MHz</mi></math></p><p>Radio signal&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8594;</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>MHz</mi></math></p><p>High quality music&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8594;</mo><mn>20</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>kHz</mi></math></p><p>Human speech&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8594;</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>kHz</mi></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (28 Jun Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":39483,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Communication System","question":"","options":["20","10","8","15"],"answer":1,"solution":"Given, modulating frequency $f_m$ $=15 \\mathrm{KHz}$\n$\\therefore \\quad$ Bandwidth of one channel $=2 f_m=30 \\mathrm{kHz}$\n$\\therefore \\quad$ No of channels accommodate\n$$\n=\\frac{300 \\mathrm{kHz}}{30 \\mathrm{kHz}}=10\n$$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2018 (15 Apr Shift 1 Online)","image":null},{"id":39460,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Communication System","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>19</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>77</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>39</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>55</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>79</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>158</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math>"],"answer":1,"solution":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>D</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn><mi>R</mi><mi>h</mi></msqrt></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>D</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mrow><mn>8</mn><mi>R</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><msup><mn>45</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mrow><mn>8</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>6400</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>km</mi><mo>&#8773;</mo><mn>39</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>55</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (16 Mar Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":39418,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Communication System","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>5</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>kHz</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>20</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>kHz</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>10</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>kHz</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>kHz</mi></math>"],"answer":2,"solution":"<p>We have,&nbsp;</p><p>Message frequency&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>f</mi><mi>m</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>kHz</mi></math>&nbsp;and carrier wave frequency<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>f</mi><mi>c</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>MHz</mi></math><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>2000</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>KHz</mi></math></p><p>The resultant signal will have bandwidth of frequency given by</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced close=\"]\" open=\"[\"><mrow><mfenced><mrow><msub><mi>f</mi><mi mathvariant=\"italic\">c</mi></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>f</mi><mi mathvariant=\"italic\">m</mi></msub></mrow></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mfenced><mrow><msub><mi>f</mi><mi mathvariant=\"italic\">c</mi></msub><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>f</mi><mi mathvariant=\"italic\">m</mi></msub></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfenced></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mo>[</mo><mo>(</mo><mn>2000</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>)</mo><mo>-</mo><mo>(</mo><mn>2000</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>)</mo><mo>]</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>kHz</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>10</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>kHz</mi></math>.</p><p>Thus, bandwidth for amplitude modulation is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>10</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>kHz</mi></math>.</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (25 Jan Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":39423,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Communication System","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>220</mn><mi>kHz</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>180</mn><mi>kHz</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>360</mn><mi>kHz</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>440</mn><mi>kHz</mi></math>"],"answer":3,"solution":"<blockquote><p>Given</p><p>FM broadcast</p><p>Modulating frequency <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>20</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>kHz</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>f</mi></math></p><p>Deviation ratio <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>frequency</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>deviation</mi><mo>&#160;</mo></mrow><mrow><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>modulating</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>frequency</mi><mo>&#160;</mo></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mo>&#8710;</mo><mi>f</mi></mrow><mi>f</mi></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo></math> Frequency deviation,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#916;</mi><mi>f</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>f</mi><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>10</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>20</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>kHz</mi><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>10</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>200</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>kHz</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo></math> Bandwidth <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mfenced><mrow><mi>f</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>&#916;</mi><mi>f</mi></mrow></mfenced></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mfenced><mrow><mn>20</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>200</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>kHz</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>440</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>kHz</mi></math></p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (28 Jul Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":39445,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Communication System","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>h</mi><mi>r</mi></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>h</mi><mi>t</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>160</mn></math> (Given)<br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>LOS</mi><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>2</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">R</mi></msqrt><mfenced><mrow><msqrt><msub><mi>h</mi><mi>r</mi></msub></msqrt><mo>+</mo><msqrt><msub><mi>h</mi><mi>t</mi></msub></msqrt></mrow></mfenced></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>LOS</mi><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>2</mn><mi>R</mi></msqrt><mfenced><mrow><msqrt><msub><mi>h</mi><mi>r</mi></msub></msqrt><mo>+</mo><msqrt><mn>160</mn><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>h</mi><mi>r</mi></msub></msqrt></mrow></mfenced></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>dLOS</mi><mrow><mi>d</mi><msub><mi>h</mi><mi>r</mi></msub></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>2</mn><mi>R</mi></msqrt><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mn>2</mn><msqrt><msub><mi>h</mi><mi>r</mi></msub></msqrt></mrow></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mn>2</mn><msqrt><mn>160</mn><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>h</mi><mi>r</mi></msub></msqrt></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>h</mi><mi>r</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>h</mi><mi>t</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>80</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>LOS</mo><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>2</mn><mi>R</mi></msqrt><mo>(</mo><msqrt><mn>80</mn></msqrt><mo>+</mo><msqrt><mn>80</mn></msqrt><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>6400</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>80</mn></msqrt><mo>=</mo><mn>64</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>km</mi></math>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (31 Aug Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":39467,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Communication System","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi><mo>,</mo><mn>5</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>5</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>8</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>5</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi><mo>,</mo><mn>8</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi><mo>,</mo><mn>5</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi></math>"],"answer":1,"solution":"<p>From Given Equation</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#956;</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>6</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>A</mi><mi>m</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mi>&#956;</mi><mi>A</mi><mi>c</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><msub><mi>A</mi><mi>max</mi></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>A</mi><mi>min</mi></msub></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>A</mi><mi>c</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><msub><mi>A</mi><mi>max</mi></msub><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>A</mi><mi>min</mi></msub></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi></math></p><p>From Equation (1) + (2)</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>A</mi><mi>max</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi></math></p><p>From Equation (1) &ndash; (2)</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>A</mi><mi>min</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi></math></p><p>&nbsp;</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2020 (02 Sep Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":39431,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Communication System","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>500</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>375</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>250</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>125</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math>"],"answer":1,"solution":"<p>Maximum distance covered is given by&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>d</mi><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>2</mn><mi>R</mi><mi>h</mi></msqrt></math>, here&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>R</mi></math>&nbsp;is the radius.</p><p>Now, to increase the length of radio transmission to&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn></math>&nbsp;times,<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mi>d</mi><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>2</mn><msup><mi>h</mi><mo>&#39;</mo></msup><mi>R</mi></msqrt></math></p><p>Height of tower is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>h</mi><mo>&#39;</mo></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>h</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>125</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>500</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math></p>\n\\(\\begin{aligned} \\Delta H=h^{\\prime}-h &=500-125 \\\\ &=375 \\end{aligned}\\)","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (29 Jun Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":39484,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Communication System","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>15</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>20</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>8</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>10</mn></math>"],"answer":3,"solution":"If modulating frequency is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>15</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>kHz</mi><mo>&#160;</mo></math>then&nbsp;the bandwidth of one channel <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>30</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>kHz</mi></math>. A number of channels accommodate. <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>300</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>kHz</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>30</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>kHz</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>10</mn></math>.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2018 (15 Apr)","image":null},{"id":39399,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Communication System","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mi>&#955;</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>&#955;</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>&#955;</mi><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#955;</mi></math>"],"answer":2,"solution":"<blockquote><p>For efficient radiation and reception, the height of transmitting and receiving antennas should be comparable to a quarter of wavelength of the frequency used. So for efficient transmission of signals of wavelengths<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>&#955;</mi></math>&nbsp;the minimum length of antenna should be&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>&#955;</mi><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math>.</p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (13 Apr Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":39442,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Communication System","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>42</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>42</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>mm</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>21</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>mm</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>21</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math>"],"answer":2,"solution":"<p>The wavelength of the carrier wave is,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>&#955;</mi><mi>c</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>c</mi><msub><mi>&#957;</mi><mi>c</mi></msub></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>8</mn></msup></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>9</mn></msup></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>35</mn></mfrac><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math>.</p><p>The minimum size of the antenna required is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mrow><mi>t</mi><mi>h</mi></mrow></msup></math>&nbsp;of the wavelength of the carrier. Therefore,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>l</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mo>&#215;</mo><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>35</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>21</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>mm</mi></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (24 Jun Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":39470,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Communication System","question":"","options":["proportional to carrier frequency","independent of both carrier and modulation frequency","inversely proportional to modulation frequency","inversely proportional to carrier frequency"],"answer":3,"solution":"The physical sizes of transmitter and receiver antenna are directly proportional to carrier wave wavelength or inversely proportional to carrier wave frequency.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (09 Apr Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":39406,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Communication System","question":"","options":["&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>l</mi><mi>&#955;</mi></mfrac></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mfenced><mfrac><mi>l</mi><mi>&#955;</mi></mfrac></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>l</mi><msup><mi>&#955;</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><msup><mi>l</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>&#955;</mi></mfrac></math>"],"answer":1,"solution":"<blockquote><p>Linear antennas are considered to be those antennas that imply the use of electrically thin conductors having diameter much less than the wavelength of the electromagnetic wave passing through them.</p><p>The formula to calculate the effective power radiated by a linear antenna is given by</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>P</mi><mrow><mi>e</mi><mi>f</mi><mi>f</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mi>k</mi><mfrac><msup><mi>l</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><msup><mi>&#955;</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac></math></p><p>where,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>k</mi></math>&nbsp;is a constant.</p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (08 Apr Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":39504,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Communication System","question":"","options":["Optical fibres can be of graded refractive index","Optical fibres are subjective to electromagnetic interference from outside","Optical fibres have extremely low transmission loss","Optical fibres may have homogeneous core with a suitable cladding."],"answer":1,"solution":"No Solution Available","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2003","image":null},{"id":39411,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Communication System","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>106</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>M</mi><mi>H</mi><mi>z</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>64</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>M</mi><mi>H</mi><mi>z</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>99</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>M</mi><mi>H</mi><mi>z</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>89</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>M</mi><mi>H</mi><mi>z</mi></math>"],"answer":1,"solution":"<p>Sound waves of different frequencies can be used in different purposes.&nbsp;FM broadcasting frequently makes use of frequency modulation. Additionally, it is utilised in telemetry, radar, seismic prospecting, EEG-based seizure monitoring of neonates, two-way radio systems, sound synthesis, magnetic tape recording, and some video transmission systems.</p><p>The range for FM broadcasting lies between&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>88</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>MHz</mi></math>&nbsp;to&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>108</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>MHz</mi></math>.</p><p>Hence,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>64</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>MHz</mi></math>&nbsp;does not belong to the FM broadcast.</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (01 Feb Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":39437,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Communication System","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>25</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>20</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>10</mn></math>"],"answer":3,"solution":"<p>Here, modulation index,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#956;</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>A</mi><mi>m</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>A</mi><mi>c</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>20</mn><mn>40</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math></p><p>Modulated amplitude <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>&#956;</mi><mi>Ac</mi></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>&#215;</mo><mfrac><mn>40</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>10</mn></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (26 Jun Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":39477,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Communication System","question":"","options":["1785 and 1715","$178.5$ and $171.5$","$89.25$ and $85.75$","$892.5$ and $857.5$"],"answer":2,"solution":"Equation given<br>$$<br>\\begin{array}{l}<br>\\mathrm{V}(\\mathrm{t})=10\\left[1+0.3 \\cos \\left(2.2 \\times 10^{4}\\right)\\right] \\\\<br>\\sin \\left(5.5 \\times 10^{5} \\mathrm{t}\\right) \\\\<br>=10+1.5\\left[\\sin \\left(57.2 \\times 10^{4} \\mathrm{t}\\right)+\\sin \\left(52.8 \\times 10^{4} \\mathrm{t}\\right)\\right] \\\\<br>\\omega_{\\mathrm{c}}+\\omega_{\\mathrm{w}}=57.2 \\times 10^{4}=2 \\pi \\mathrm{f}_{1}<br>\\end{array}<br>$$<br>$$<br>\\mathrm{f}_{1}=\\frac{57.2 \\times 10^{4}}{2 \\times\\left(\\frac{22}{7}\\right)}=9.1 \\times 10^{4} \\simeq 91 \\mathrm{KHz}<br>$$<br>$$<br>\\omega_{\\mathrm{c}}-\\omega_{\\mathrm{w}}=52.8 \\times 10^{4}<br>$$<br>$$<br>\\mathrm{f}_{2}=\\frac{52.8 \\times 10^{4}}{2 \\times\\left(\\frac{22}{7}\\right)} \\simeq 84 \\mathrm{KHz}<br>$$<br><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/2MM9nZpPivhVAd4drFNV5pSRrw_17zXhcr8Lb24vld4.original.fullsize.png\"><br>Upper side band frequency $\\left(f_{1}\\right)$ is <br>$$<br>\\mathrm{f}_{1}=\\mathrm{f}_{\\mathrm{c}}-\\mathrm{f}_{\\mathrm{w}}=\\frac{52.8 \\times 10^{4}}{2 \\pi} \\approx 85.00 \\mathrm{kHz}<br>$$<br>Lower side band frequency $\\left(\\mathrm{f}_{2}\\right)$ is<br>$$<br>\\mathrm{f}_{2}=\\mathrm{f}_{\\mathrm{c}}+\\mathrm{f}_{\\mathrm{w}}=\\frac{57.2 \\times 10^{4}}{2 \\pi} \\approx 90.00 \\mathrm{kHz}<br>$$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (11 Jan Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":39482,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Communication System","question":"","options":["$18 \\mathrm{kHz}-30 \\mathrm{kHz}$","$63 \\mathrm{kHz}-75 \\mathrm{kHz}$","$442 \\mathrm{kHz}-466 \\mathrm{kHz}$","$13482 \\mathrm{kHz}-13494 \\mathrm{kHz}$"],"answer":2,"solution":"Given: Inductance, $L=49 \\mu \\mathrm{H}=49 \\times 10^{-6} \\mathrm{H}$, capacitance $C=2.5 \\mathrm{nF}=2.5 \\times 10^{-9} \\mathrm{~F}$\n$$\n\\begin{aligned}\n&\\text { Using } \\omega=\\frac{1}{\\sqrt{L C}} \\\\\n&=\\frac{1}{\\sqrt{49 \\times 10^{-6} \\times \\frac{2.5}{10} \\times 10^{-9}}} \\\\\n&=\\frac{1}{7 \\times 5 \\times 10^{-8}}=\\frac{10^8}{7 \\times 5} \\\\\n&\\text { or, } \\frac{10^8}{7 \\times 5}=2 \\pi \\times f=2 \\times \\frac{22}{7} \\times f \\\\\n&\\text { or, } f=\\frac{10^7}{22}=\\frac{10^4}{22} \\mathrm{kHz}=454.54 \\mathrm{kHz}\n\\end{aligned}\n$$\nTherefore frequency range $454.54 \\pm 12 \\mathrm{kHz}$ i.e., $442 \\mathrm{kHz}-466 \\mathrm{kHz}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2018 (15 Apr Shift 2 Online)","image":null},{"id":39452,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Communication System","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>Modulation index</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#956;</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><msub><mi>A</mi><mi>m</mi></msub><msub><mi>A</mi><mi>c</mi></msub></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>20</mn><mn>20</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (25 Jul Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":39398,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Communication System","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>96</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>km</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>56</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>km</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>48</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>km</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>104</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>km</mi></math>"],"answer":3,"solution":"<blockquote><p>The maximum distance for line of sight communication is&nbsp;</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>d</mi><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>2</mn><mi>h</mi><mi>R</mi></msqrt><mo>+</mo><msqrt><mn>2</mn><mi>h</mi><mo>&#39;</mo><mi>R</mi></msqrt></math></p><p>The given data is&nbsp;</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>R</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>6400</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>km</mi><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mi>h</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>180</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi><mo>&#39;</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>245</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math></p><p>Thus, the value is</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>d</mi><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>2</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>180</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>6400</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>3</mn></msup></msqrt></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>+</mo><msqrt><mn>2</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>245</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>6400</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>3</mn></msup></msqrt></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>80</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>7</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>80</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>2</mn></msup></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>104</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>km</mi></math></p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (15 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":39451,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Communication System","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>In radio communications, a sideband is a band of frequencies higher than or lower than the carrier frequency, that are the result of the modulation process.&nbsp;The signal components&nbsp;above the carrier frequency constitute the upper sideband (USB), and those below the carrier frequency constitute the lower sideband (LSB).</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/119962ca-b8fa-4e54-ad91-801d290270cc-image.png\" style=\"width: 304px; height: 188px;\" /></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>a</mi><mn>10</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>b</mi><mn>10</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>&#956;</mi><msub><mi>A</mi><mi>C</mi></msub></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mfrac><mi>a</mi><mi>b</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (27 Jul Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":39405,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Communication System","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>5</mn></math>"],"answer":1,"solution":"<blockquote><p>The given data is&nbsp;</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>A</mi><mi>c</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>15</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><msub><mi>A</mi><mi>m</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi></math></p><p>Thus, the maximum amplitude and minimum amplitude is&nbsp;</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>A</mi><mrow><mi>m</mi><mi>a</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>A</mi><mi>c</mi></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>A</mi><mi>m</mi></msub><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><msub><mi>A</mi><mrow><mi>m</mi><mi>i</mi><mi>n</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>A</mi><mi>c</mi></msub><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>A</mi><mi>m</mi></msub></math></p><p>Hence, the ratio is&nbsp;</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><msub><mi>A</mi><mi>max</mi></msub><msub><mi>A</mi><mi>min</mi></msub></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>15</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>15</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>18</mn><mn>12</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mfenced></math></p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (10 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":39495,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Communication System","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>45</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>km</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>54</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>km</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>55</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>km</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>455</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>km</mi></math>"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>Given,</p><p>Height of transmitting&nbsp;antenna is,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>h</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>50</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math></p><p>Height of receiving antenna is,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>h</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">R</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>32</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math></p><p>Thus,&nbsp;maximum distance for satisfactory communication will be,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>d</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">M</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>2</mn><mi>R</mi><msub><mi>h</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi></msub></msqrt><mo>+</mo><msqrt><mn>2</mn><mi>R</mi><msub><mi>h</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">R</mi></msub></msqrt></math>&nbsp;where&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>R</mi></math>&nbsp;is radius of the Earth,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>d</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">M</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>2</mn><mi>R</mi><msub><mi>h</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi></msub></msqrt><mo>+</mo><msqrt><mn>2</mn><mi>R</mi><msub><mi>h</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">R</mi></msub></msqrt><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><msub><mi>d</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">M</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>2</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>64</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>5</mn></msup><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>50</mn></msqrt><mo>+</mo><msqrt><mn>2</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>64</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>5</mn></msup><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>32</mn></msqrt><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><msub><mi>d</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">M</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>8000</mn><msqrt><mn>10</mn></msqrt><mo>+</mo><mn>6400</mn><msqrt><mn>10</mn></msqrt><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><msub><mi>d</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">M</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>14400</mn><msqrt><mn>10</mn></msqrt><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><msub><mi>d</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">M</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>45536</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>7</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><msub><mi>d</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">M</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>45</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>km</mi></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2014 (09 Apr Online)","image":null},{"id":39450,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Communication System","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>A</mi><mi>max</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>A</mi><mi mathvariant=\"italic\">c</mi></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>A</mi><mi mathvariant=\"italic\">m</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>12</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>A</mi><mi>min</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>A</mi><mi>c</mi></msub><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>A</mi><mi>m</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><msub><mi>A</mi><mi mathvariant=\"italic\">c</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>15</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mrow><mo mathvariant=\"italic\">&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"italic\">A</mi></mrow><mi mathvariant=\"italic\">m</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>9</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math></p><p>Modulation index <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><msub><mi mathvariant=\"italic\">A</mi><mi mathvariant=\"italic\">m</mi></msub><msub><mi mathvariant=\"italic\">A</mi><mi mathvariant=\"italic\">c</mi></msub></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mn>9</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mstyle><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mn>15</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mstyle></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>6</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (27 Jul Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":39473,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Communication System","question":"","options":["<math><mn>2400</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\"> </mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math>","<math><mn>900</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\"> </mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math>","<math><mn>600</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\"> </mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math>","<math><mn>1500</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\"> </mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math>"],"answer":3,"solution":"For minimum attenuation, the wavelength of carrier waves is close to <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1500</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (08 Apr Shift 1)","image":null}]